@node Introduction "Introduction"

                                 @{b}Introduction@{ub}

    This program writes text files by incredible fashion. This is like
Type command, but in other edition. Program was made to fun. You may be
want to make someone joke and send to him or her file, what is changed by
this program.

@endnode

@node Instructions "Instructions"

                                 @{b}Instructions@{ub}

    You should run this program from CLI/Shell. Parameters:
 - READFILE/A - must be, this is a file from program shows chars in CLI
window.
 - SAVEFILE - if you want you may save chars to this file;
 - DOUBLE/S - if you want see, how its run you must give SAVEFILE, this is
writing chars to file and to CON.

    If you run program with "?" then you see all parameters. You may stop
the program by pressing Ctrl+C. Program shows chars using Escape's codes.

@endnode

@node Requirements "System requirements"

                                 @{b}Requirements@{ub}

    Program is running on Amiga with Kickstart 1.3 and 512KB of memory. It
is using "dos.library". Program was wrote on the A1200 with HD and 4MB
Fast in AmigaE v3.2a.

@endnode

@node Errors "Error messages"

                                @{b}Error Messages@{ub}

    Error messages:
 - Bad Args! - you give bad arguments, see @{" Instructions " link Instructions};
 - I can't open xxx! - program can't open file from chars will be reads;
 - You break me! - you pressed Ctrl+C;
 - Lenght of xxx is 0! - file lenght is NUL and program can't reads chars
from file;
 - I can't open xxx file to save! - program can't open file to save chars
from first file;
 - I can't save to xxx! - may be disk is full.

@endnode

@node Instalation "Instalation"

                                 @{b}Instalation@{ub}

    Just copy the drawer with program and with docs to your drawer. Then
copy "Kropka" file to C: directory.

@endnode

@node Future "What's in future"

                              @{b}What's in future?@{ub}

    Writes file with changing font and font size.

@endnode

